<div id="main" class="clearfix"><div id="container" class="no-sidebar"><div id="content"><article id="post-1117" class="clearfix post-1117 page type-page status-publish hentry" role="article"><div class="entry-content clearfix"><section  class="wpb_row main_row  no-seperator" style="text-align:center; background-color:#2d7bbf; background-image:url(../wp-content/uploads/2018/03/on-the-tablet.jpg); padding-top:50px; padding-bottom:50px; background-repeat:no-repeat; background-position:Center center;"><div class="row-inner"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner vc_custom_1521730422657"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " ><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h1 class="main-page-title">What is KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 16px;">®</sup> Escrow?</h1></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section  class="wpb_row main_row  no-seperator hide_tablet_portrait hide_mobile_landscape hide_mobile_portrait" style="text-align:right; padding-top:70px; padding-bottom:70px;"><div class="row-inner"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-8"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " ><div class="wpb_wrapper"><h2 class="title-faq">Everything You Need to Know About KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 14px;">®</sup> Escrow</h2></div></div></div></div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-4"><div class="vc_column-inner "><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="vc_empty_space"   style="height: 51px" ><span class="vc_empty_space_inner"></span></div> <a class="wpb_button_a" href="../contact-page/index.html" title=""><span class="wpb_button wpb_btn_orange wpb_btn-large get-started"> <i class="fa fa-envelope"></i>Can't find the answer? </span></a></div></div></div></div></section><section  class="wpb_row main_row  row-line-seperator ipad_full_width" style="background-color:#fafafa; padding-top:70px; padding-bottom:50px;"><div class="row-inner"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner vc_custom_1411717326799"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " ><div class="wpb_wrapper"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> works as a neutral third party that provides financial protection for both buyers and sellers. Using online escrow accounts, we collect, hold and disburse funds upon both parties’ approval. Transactions are created online and agreed to by both parties, saving time and misunderstandings.</p></div></div><div class="vc_empty_space"   style="height: 32px" ><span class="vc_empty_space_inner"></span></div><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " ><div class="wpb_wrapper"><p><strong>General Info</strong></p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >What does escrow mean?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Escrow is property held in trust by a neutral party in a transaction to be turned over upon fulfillment of an agreement or contract.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >What types of transactions can I use KingsTrust for?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup>’s escrow services can be used for the trading of any legal goods with the exception of real estate. We do, however, reserve the right to refuse service for any transaction.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Can I use KingsTrust for real estate transactions?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>No. Real estate transactions are restricted due to varying state regulations. This includes transactions involving deeds and timeshare ownership sales.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Can I use KingsTrust for international transactions?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Yes. KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> can be used for transactions between countries approved by the United States government for trade.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >What currencies does KingsTrust accept for international transactions?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust accepts and pays out international wires in U.S. dollars.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >How does KingsTrust make money?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup>&#8216;s fees are collected per transaction for the collection and distribution of escrowed funds.</p></div></div><div class="vc_empty_space"   style="height: 20px" ><span class="vc_empty_space_inner"></span></div><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " ><div class="wpb_wrapper"><p><strong>Safety &amp; Security</strong></p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >How does KingsTrust protect the seller?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> protects sellers by verifying all buyer purchase funds up front before any exchange of items takes place. This eliminates the risk of non-payment or insufficient funds and guarantees serious buyers &#8211; not just window-shoppers.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >How does KingsTrust protect the buyer?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> protects buyers by holding their funds in a neutral, third-party bank account until their purchase agreement is completed. Funds cannot be pushed to the seller without the buyer’s approval, protecting against misrepresentation and keeping honest people honest.</p></div></div><div class="vc_empty_space"   style="height: 20px" ><span class="vc_empty_space_inner"></span></div><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " ><div class="wpb_wrapper"><p><strong>Getting Started</strong></p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >What are the steps in the escrow process?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><ol><li>Buyer or seller creates the transaction and invites the other party.</li><li>Both parties agree to the transaction details.</li><li>Buyer funds the full escrow balance.</li><li>Seller delivers or ships the goods and requests payment</li><li>Buyer verifies the transaction terms have been met and approves the seller’s payment request</li><li>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> releases escrow funds to seller.</li></ol></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Why do I have to provide a copy of my driver’s license or passport?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> must verify all users’ identities according to our anti-money laundering policy in order to protect all parties.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >What happens if the other party rejects the transaction invitation?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>The transaction is returned to <em>Estimate</em> status and can be modified and resent by the original creator.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Can the transaction details be changed after both parties have agreed to the terms and the transaction is activated?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>No. Once the transaction is agreed upon by both parties, the transaction details are not editable.</p></div></div><div class="vc_empty_space"   style="height: 20px" ><span class="vc_empty_space_inner"></span></div><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " ><div class="wpb_wrapper"><p><strong>Funding &amp; Payment</strong></p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >How do I fund a transaction?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Once both buyer and seller have approved the transaction details, the funding instructions will be visible to the seller when securely logged in to the KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> platform. Funding instructions may be printed and provided to the bank to initiate the wire transfer. Wire transfers must be initiated from an account matching the user’s profile.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Why must funds be wired from the user’s bank account?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup>’s anti-money laundering policy requires the verification of the users’ identities and the traceability of all money transfers to the accountable parties.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Will KingsTrust email me the funding instructions?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>No. Funding instruction are only visible while securely logged in to your KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> account.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >What payment methods do you accept?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> buyers provide funds via bank wire transfers.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >How does a seller request payment?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Sellers initiate the release of escrow funds by requesting payment while logged into their KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> account. After clicking the “payment request” button, the seller will input both the amount requested and their bank account information.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >When do escrow funds get released?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> only releases escrow funds at the specific requests of both the buyer and seller. Both parties should agree to expectations regarding the release of funds in the transaction details.</p><p>Examples:</p><ul><li>Once the goods are shipped</li><li>Once the transportation company confirms pick-up</li><li>Once the goods are received and inspected by the buyer</li></ul></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Can KingsTrust release money to someone other than the seller account profile?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>No. KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> will only release funds to a bank account owned by the user.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >When does the seller get paid?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Once the buyer approves the payment request, KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> will process the seller&#8217;s automated clearing house (ACH) payment during normal banking hours (usually Monday through Friday, 9-5 Mountain Standard Time.) The seller will typically receive the funds within two business days.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >How does the buyer request a refund?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>The buyer can request a refund after the transaction has been activated by clicking the “request refund” tab while logged into the system with the transaction details open. The request will be submitted to the seller for their approval and, once approved, KingsTrust will process the payment.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >What is an ACH transfer?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>An ACH (automated clearing house) transfer is the electronic transfer of funds processed by the National Automated Clearing House Association, an electronic network of financial institutions.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >What happens if the buyer never logs in and releases the funds?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> can approve the release of funds as long as the seller has carried out the purchase agreement to completion and there is no dispute in progress. These types of requests are dealt with on a case-by-case basis. Please contact a service representative at (877) 638-1518 or <a href="mailto:support@KingsTrustescrow.com">support@KingsTrustescrow.com</a> for more details.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >How long will it take until funds appear in the seller’s account?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>ACH (Automated Clearing House) payments will take 24-48 hours to show in the seller’s account dependent on banking business hours. All payments initiated prior to 3 p.m. Central Time will be processed the same business day. Payments initiated after 3 p.m. Central Time will be processed on the next business day.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Why haven’t the buyer’s funds shown up in my account?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>If you were notified that your transaction has been processed, but no deposit has shown in your account for three business days, please contact us at (877) 638-1518 or <a href="mailto:support@KingsTrustescrow.com">support@KingsTrustescrow.com</a>.</p><p>Please note that payments initiated on Fridays after 3 p.m. Central Time will not be processed until the following bank business day &#8211; generally Monday morning barring any federal holidays.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Where does KingsTrust keep my funds held in escrow?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Escrowed funds are held in highly-rated, FDIC-insured United States financial institutions and are disbursed only upon agreement by both parties.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Can I make partial payments?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Yes. Partial payments can be made should the seller request only a portion of the total transaction amount. Partial payments are up to the discretion of both buyer and seller.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Is there a fee for partial payments?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Yes. Payments for less than the full purchase or sale amount will incur a $25 charge due to processing fees charged by financial institutions for additional incoming and outgoing wires. If you have questions about this, please contact us at (877) 638-1518 or <a href="mailto:support@KingsTrustescrow.com">support@KingsTrustescrow.com</a>.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Is there a fee for international payments?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Yes. International payments will incur a $40 charge due to processing fees charged by financial institutions for international fund transfers. If you have questions about this, please contact us at (877) 638-1518 or <a href="mailto:support@KingsTrustescrow.com">support@KingsTrustescrow.com</a>.</p></div></div><div class="vc_empty_space"   style="height: 20px" ><span class="vc_empty_space_inner"></span></div><div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " ><div class="wpb_wrapper"><p><strong>Shipping &amp; Transport</strong></p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Who is responsible for shipping?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>Either party can arrange and/or pay for shipping or vehicle transportation, but this should be agreed upon prior to completing the transaction.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Does KingsTrust collect transportation costs?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> cannot pay third-party transportation costs. All funds are released to users’ bank accounts. It is highly recommended that users pay transportation costs outside of the escrow transaction.</p></div></div><div  class="vc_toggle vc_toggle_default vc_toggle_color_default  vc_toggle_size_md"><div class="vc_toggle_title"><h2 style="font-size: 14px;color: #575757;text-align: left" class="vc_custom_heading" >Is KingsTrust a shipping company?</h2><i class="vc_toggle_icon"></i></div><div class="vc_toggle_content"><p>No. KingsTrust<sup style="font-size: 9px;">®</sup> does not play a role in the shipping or transportation of any items, but we can recommend trusted partners who are some of the best in the industry.</p><p>For more information, visit our <a href="../index.html">Transportation page</a